# Go Linting

When working with Go code, run the linter yourself rather than relying solely on
IDE diagnostics. This provides more accurate and complete feedback.

## Commands

Format code:

```shell
go tool golangci-lint fmt ./...
```

Lint code:

```shell
go tool golangci-lint run ./...
```

## Workflow

**Always run the formatter before the linter.** The formatter fixes issues that
would otherwise appear as lint errors.

1. Run `go tool golangci-lint fmt ./...` to auto-format
2. Run `go tool golangci-lint run ./...` to check for remaining issues
3. Fix any reported problems

## When to Run

Run the formatter and linter:

- After making substantive edits to Go files
