  better insight into the actual issues
- Before considering a task complete

## Targeting Specific Files

For faster feedback on specific files or packages:

```shell
go tool golangci-lint fmt path/to/file.go
go tool golangci-lint run path/to/package/...
```

## Notes

- The IDE will not show all lint errors. Run the commands manually to see all
issues.
- The IDE will not refresh the lint errors when you save the file. The commands
are the source of truth. If the IDE finds linter issues after running the
commands, ignore the IDE's errors.
